subSubSection.paragraph:
Mouth large, oblique; maxilla extending to below middle of lower eye; anterior tip of upper jaw beyond tip of lower jaw when mouth closed. Teeth on upper jaw uniserial, rather strong, anterior 4–6 enlarged, canine-like; lower jaw teeth uniserial, canine anteriorly, strong conical laterally, stronger than upper lateral teeth; anterior teeth on upper jaws extruded beyond tip of lower jaws (
Fig. 18A
). Gill rakers on first arch short and flattened, inner margin of each raker with 2–5 stout spines, no gill rakers on upper limb (
Fig. 18B
). Ocular-side scales ctenoid with short ctenii, moderate and deciduous; tips of both jaws and ocular side of snout naked; scales cycloid on blind side.
